SIMPLE: subtlety
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtlety
<hw>Sub"tle*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Subtleties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>sotelte</ets>,
<ets>sutilte</ets>, OF. <ets>sotillete</ets>, L. <ets>subtilitas</ets>.
See <er>Subtle</er>, and cf. <er>Subtility</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or state of being subtle, or sly; cunning; craftiness;
artfulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fox which lives by <qex>subtlety</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nice discernment with delicacy of mental action;
nicety of discrimination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something that is sly, crafty, or
delusive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unlearned in the world's false <qex>subtleties</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtly</ent>⟦br⟧
